pahdatabase.comment:
This is the NASA Ames PAH IR Spectroscopic Database. The contents of the database are described in Bauschlicher et al. (2010) and Boersma et al. (2014). The database website is located at http://localhost/PAHdb/.
You are kindly asked to cite the following papers when using the database:
Boersma, C., Bauschlicher, C.W., Jr., Ricca, A., Mattioda, A. L., Cami, J., Peeters, E., Sánchez de Armas, F., Puerta Saborido, G., Hudgins, D M., and Allamandola, L.J., "The NASA Ames PAH IR Spectroscopic database version 2.00: updated content, website and on/offline tools", 2014, The Astrophysical Journal Supplement Series, 211, 8
A copy of the paper can be downloaded from NASA's ADS services:
http://adsabs.harvard.edu/cgi-bin/nph-data_query?bibcode=2014ApJS..211....8B&link_type=ARTICLE&db_key=AST&nocookies=1
Bauschlicher, C.W., Jr., Boersma, C., Ricca, A., Mattioda, A. L., Cami, J., Peeters, E., Sánchez de Armas, F., Puerta Saborido, G., Hudgins, D M., and Allamandola, L.J., "The NASA Ames Polycyclic Aromatic Hydrocarbon Infrared Spectroscopic Database: The Computed Spectra", 2010, The Astrophysical Journal Supplement Series, 189, 341
A copy of the paper can be downloaded from NASA's ADS services:
http://adsabs.harvard.edu/cgi-bin/nph-data_query?bibcode=2010ApJS..189..341B&link_type=ARTICLE&db_key=AST&nocookies=1
Mattioda, A.L., Hudgins, D.M., Boersma, C., Ricca, A., Peeters, E., Cami, J., Sánches de Armas, F., Puerta Saborido, G., Bauschlicher, C W., J., and Allamandola, L.J. "The Nasa Ames PAH IR Spectroscopic Database: The Laboratory Spectra", in preparation
Also see http://localhost/PAHdb/theoretical/3.10/help/citation. Notes: Theoretical database This version has multiple scale factors and the Gaussian options for each run are more fully described. A large number of new species have been added, including species with 5- and 7- membered rings, additional oval species, species with bay regions, species with side groups, some acridene species, and the neutral species from Mackie et al. (2015), with 1525 CnHm and 803 fully dehydrogenates species.

references.reference: Ricca, A., Bauschlicher, C.W., Jr., Boersma, C., Tielens, A.G.G.M., Allamandola, L.J., "The Infrared Spectroscopy of Compact Polycyclic Aromatic Hydrocarbons Containing Up To 384 Carbons", 2012, ApJ, 754, 75 doi:10.1088/0004-637x/754/1/75
Langhoff, S.R., "Theoretical Infrared Spectra for Polycyclic Aromatic Hydrocarbon Neutrals, Cations, and Anions", 1996, J. Phys. Chem., 100, 2819 doi:10.1021/jp952074g
